    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look to capitalize on several favorable matchups today, with **Gunnar Henderson** headlining the card. His massive 83.29 efficiency score is fueled by a dynamic platoon advantage against Sandy Alcantara and the benefit of leading off, making him our primary engine for production. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) and **Josh Lowe** (72.21) also offer high-floor outcomes today. Specifically, **Josh Lowe** is a priority start despite the lower lineup spot because he draws a soft matchup against Erick Fedde, and his propensity for stolen bases against slow deliveries provides a crucial boost in our scarcest category. Meanwhile, **Nolan Schanuel** (69.91) benefits significantly from favorable winds and a weak opponent in Fedde, solidifying his role in the heart of the lineup.\n\nOur most difficult decision centered on the bench, where **Marcell Ozuna** (61.28) and **Brady House** (61.05) both posted stronger projections than several active starters. **Marcell Ozuna** was edged out primarily due to the optimizer prioritizing defensive flexibility and the specific platoon benefits associated with our active starters against pitchers like Taj Bradley. While **Marcell Ozuna** possesses elite power, the current configuration maximizes our volume of stolen base opportunities and neutralizes potential negative platoon splits. We remain wary of the \"Lineup Pending\" status for all starters, particularly with **Liam Hicks** and **Drake Baldwin**; should the actual batting orders shift downward, we may see further efficiency degradation, especially for **Jackson Merrill** and **Kyle Tucker**, who are already facing stiff resistance from Logan Webb and Peter Lambert, respectively.",
